The heat H (J) available in 1-km-thick basement (starting at a depth of 5 km) below this potential area of 89,000 km 2 is evaluated as 9078 EJ using the relation: 
						(13)H=ρr·cp·V·(Tx−Tr)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
								 $$ H = \rho_{r}\cdot c_{p}\cdot V\cdot (T_{x} - T_{r})  $$ 
							\end{document}

For an EGS plant’s operational life of 31 years, the theoretical potential electric power Pp (W e) (Beardsmore et al. 2010) is evaluated as 928 GW e using the relation: 
						(14)Pp=(H·ηt)/(31·365·86,400)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}
								 $$ P_{p} = (H\cdot\eta_{t}) / (31\cdot 365\cdot 86,400)  $$ 
							\end{document}
